OL,3,CRough sleepers behind new film calling
OL,4,Cfor homelessness reform
OL,6,FBased in North Shields, Mr Charlton
OL,7,Fwas on and off the streets himself for
OL,8,F25 years.
OL,10,FHe faced violence in his home and grew
OL,11,Fup in care and foster homes. Later, Mr
OL,12,FCharlton battled substance and alcohol
OL,13,Faddiction, but began selling the 'Big
OL,14,FIssue' and turned his life around.
OL,16,FHe told ITV Tyne Tees being homeless
OL,17,F"takes your spirit away, it rips
OL,18,Feverything, your dignity, your pride,
OL,19,Fyour self worth" and "I ended up
OL,20,Ftaking drugs and alcohol just to get
OL,21,Fthrough the day and night".
